/*
 * Smart_Probe_H2_v2_fixed.cpp
 * ============================================================
 * Root-cause fixes for the 69 ppm vs 100 ppm discrepancy:
 *
 *  FIX 1 — EMF scaling (was the primary bug):
 *    sensor_final_output after read_sensor() is in integer µV units
 *    (raw_adc / 4096 * 1000 − Reference_Set_Value).
 *    Python reads col-2 of the original log as mV with 3 dp, i.e.
 *    sensor_final_output / 1000.0.  The old run_mode() subtracted
 *    Reference_Set_Value a second time AND divided by 1000, giving
 *    wildly wrong EMF → wrong P_clip → 69 ppm instead of 100 ppm.
 *    Fix: emf_mv = (float)sensor_final_output / 1000.0f  (one step).
 *
 *  FIX 2 — calib_interp precision:
 *    Python: round(y0 + t*(y1-y0))  — all float, rounded at the end.
 *    Old C:  (long)((float)y0 + t*(float)(y1-y0) + 0.5f)
 *    The cast (float)y0 for large integers (e.g. 20000, 100000) loses
 *    precision when combined with small t values.  Fix: keep y0/y1
 *    as long, do the interpolation entirely in double/float, round last.
 *
 *  FIX 3 — P_clip (Pv) update rule:
 *    Python: Pv[i] = N_[i]  when O_[i] != O_[i-1]  (counter ticking)
 *            Pv[i] = Pv[i-1] when O_[i] == O_[i-1]  (counter capped)
 *    Old C used O_prev correctly but the comparison was applied after
 *    the O_roc update, which is correct.  Verified — no change needed.
 *
 *  FIX 4 — params_ee_load() safety:
 *    If EEPROM magic is absent (first boot or corrupt), hard-reset P
 *    to DEFAULT_PARAMS so o_cap=80 and n_thresh=0.002 are guaranteed.
 *    This prevents stale EEPROM garbage from silently breaking the engine.
 *
 *  FIX 5 — sensor_final_output kept as long long:
 *    Changed from float to long long to match original Smart_Probe.cpp
 *    integer arithmetic, preventing float rounding before the /1000.
 *
 *  FIX 6 — raw_sensor_uv saved before reference subtraction:
 *    Enables col-2 (RawEMF) output without re-reading the ADC.
 *
 * 9-Column UART output (space-separated, CRLF):
 *  [1] RefR         – Reference_Set_Value
 *  [2] EMF_mV       – ref-subtracted EMF in mV, 3 dp (what engine sees,
 *                     identical to Python col-2 / str3)
 *  [3] DispPPM      – S = max(Q,R) integer
 *  [4] Type         – F or A
 *  [5] H2_Flag      – AIR_L / AIR_H / UP / DOWN / REC
 *  [6] Rec_Status   – 100_L / 100_H / integer %
 *  [7] OR_Status    – NORMAL / OVERRANGE / WAIT_DROP / PRESS_TARE
 *  [8] Warmup       – 0-4
 *  [9] PostCnt      – post-high counter (0 when inactive)
 */

